@ENDNODE


@NODE "DownloadPrefs-LOAD" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}LOAD@{uu}

 Will put the message in the @{"STATUS" LINK "DownloadPrefs-Status"} of loading.
 The pictures of this message will be loaded the next time.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-WAIT" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}WAIT@{uu}

 This will put the message in the @{"STATUS" LINK "DownloadPrefs-Status"} of WAIT.
 The pictures of this message won't get loaded the next time.  They will be
 left out.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-READ" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}READ@{uu}

 DownloadPrefs will tell YAM to show the mail of current interest.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-DELETE" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}DELETE@{uu}

 With this order you can delete an email from the list.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-END" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}END@{uu}

 You will go to the end.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs->>" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}>>@{uu}

 Go forward five mails.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs->" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}>@{uu}

 Go to the next mail.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-<" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}<@{uu}

 Go to the last mail.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-<<" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}<<@{uu}

 Go backwards five mails.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-TOP" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}TOP@{uu}

 Go to the beginning.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-DATE" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}DATE@{uu}

 DATE will show you the time when you got the mail.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-MAILPART" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}MAILPART@{uu}

 This shows you the MailPart for which you are going to load the pictures.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-SUBJECT" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}SUBJECT@{uu}

 This will show you the subject of the email.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "DownloadPrefs-FROM" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}FROM@{uu}

 FROM will show you from who you got the message.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-Status" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}STATUS@{uu}

 will show you the status of the message:

 @{"LOAD" LINK "DownloadPrefs-LOAD"} : When you open the message the next time the pictures will be loaded

 @{"WAIT" LINK "DownloadPrefs-WAIT"} : When you open the message the next time the pictures will be left out

 In brackets you can read the number of the email and how many emails there
 are altogether. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DownloadPrefs-Folder" "How to use DownloadPrefs?"

 @{u}Folder@{uu}
 Here the current folder is shown.  The mail of current interest is from this
 folder.  The emails are put in an order by folders.
 In brackets you can read the number of the current folder and the number of
 all folders.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}What are the functions of HTMLread.rexx and who needs it?@{uu}

 HTMLread.rexx is an ARexx-script which helps you to get rid of
 an annoying problem of YAM. As you know, YAM is not capable to show
 HTML-mails which are often sent from Netscape or the IE. Because of the
 HTML-tags it is pretty hard to get to read such an HTML-mail. Certainly,
 it is possible to recognize such a mail and then read it with a HTML-viewer.
 This exactly gets automated by this ARexx-script. That means if you got
 such a mail and you want to read it HTMLread.rexx will immediately
 recognize it and start the HTML-viewer. So this script can be used by
 everybody who occasionally gets such HTML-mails and wants to read them.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "What need HTMLread" "What need HTMLread?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}What need HTMLread@{uu}

 - For HTMLread you only need YAM2.1
 - DownloadManager needs (rexx)reqtools.library and MicroRexx.
 - HTMLreadPrefs needs BetterString.mcp (and of course MUI, too)

 The archive contains them and they are getting installed automatically when
 you install HTMLread.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "How to install" "How to install:"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}How to install HTMLread.rexx@{uu}

 a) Use the installer!
 b) Start YAM or click this button: @{"run YAM:YAM" SYSTEM "run YAM:YAM"}
 c) Start the configuration-window!
 d) Choose »ARexx« from the list!
 e) Choose from the list on the right side:
    »When reading a message«


 @{b}f)@{ub} Now choose ARexx and enter at »Script«:
    YAM:Rexx/checkHTML.rx

    Caution! If HTMLread doesn't react to emails which have a HTML-code,
    maybe you are using a wrong path for HTMLread.rx in checkHTML.rx. Or
    the path in @{"ENV:HTMLread" SYSTEM "type >CON:12/12/480/60/ENV:HTMLread_is_set_to:/WAIT/CLOSE env:HTMLread"} is not set or wrong.
    To set ENV:HTMLread use the two buttons:
    @{"Set ENV:HTMLread" SYSTEM "setenv ENV:HTMLread `c:RequestFile DRAWER YAM:Rexx/ FILE HTMLread.rx PATTERN #?.rx TITLE Select_(YAM:Rexx/)HTMLread.rx`"}         Open a FileRequester and set ENV:HTMLread
    @{"Copy HTMLread TO ENVARC:" SYSTEM "c:copy ENV:HTMLread ENVARC:"} Copy ENV:HTMLread TO ENVARC:HTMLread

    If line 4 is »HTMLread=""«, checkHTML.rx will use ENV:HTMLread instead. If not,
    checkHTML.rx uses the given path:
    for example »HTMLread="YAM:Rexx/HTMLread.rx"«

    I propose that you use the HTMLread file in ENV: (»HTMLread=""«)
    Start an editor:
    @{b}AmigaOS 3.5 / 3.9@{ub} @{"SYS:Tools/EditPad YAM:Rexx/checkHTML.rx" SYSTEM "SYS:Tools/EditPad YAM:Rexx/checkHTML.rx"}
    @{b}AmigaOS 2.x / 3.x@{ub} @{"C:ed YAM:Rexx/checkHTML.rx" SYSTEM "c:ed YAM:Rexx/checkHTML.rx"}

    @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"checkHTML.rx" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/checkHTML.iff/MAIN"}

    You also can use YAM:Rexx/HTMLread.rx instead of
    YAM:rexx/checkHTML.rx in the YAM Configuration. But this will slow down
    the checking of the HTMLcode.

 g) HTMLread usually uses the ConfigFile ENV:HTMLread.config
    If you want to use another ConfigFile you have to enter its name in the
    line "Script" after YAM:Rexx/HTMLread.rx. Don`t forget the
    "space" between them.

 h) Take care that the buttons: »Open console window« and
    »Wait for termination« are NOT MARKED!

    @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"YAM-Window" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/YAM-Config-read.iff/MAIN"}

 i) Choose from the list on the right side:
    »After getting mail«
 j) Now choose ARexx and enter at »Script«:
    YAM:Rexx/HRdownload.rx
 k) Take care that you DID NOT click on the button: »Open console window« and
    take care to CLICK on the button »Wait for termination«

    @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"YAM-Window" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/YAM-Config-getmail.iff/MAIN"}

 l) If you like you can also write the orders from i) to k) in:
    »After sending mail«

 m) Save!
 n) Now start @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs"}. You`ll find it at YAM:HTMLread/

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}HTMLreadPrefs@{uu}

 There are two possibilities to tell HTMLread which HTML-viewer it
 should use:
 a) You can change the ConfigFile by hand
 b) This is the easier way. You can use the HTMLreadPrefs.

 HTMLreadPrefs uses MUI with the BetterString.mcc. You can download
 BetterString from AmiNet or from the homepage:
 http://www.p2p-it.dk/duff/MCC_BetterString.LZX

 @{u}Main:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Main.iff/MAIN"}

        @{"The menu of HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Menue"}
        +@{b}---------------------------------------------------@{ub}+
        |   @{b}____________________@{ub}                            |
        |  |       Viewer       |                           |
        |  |                    +@{b}-------------------------@{ub}+ |
        |  |   +@{b}----------------------------------------@{ub}+ | |
        |  |   | @{" @| Viewer " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Viewer"} @{" Viewername              " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-ViewerName"} | | |
        |  |   +@{b}----------------------------------------@{ub}+ | |
        |  |                                              | |
        |  | Path Viewer    : @{" Path Viewer          " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Path+Viewer"} @{"#" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Path+Viewer"}   | |
        |  | Startarguements: @{" StartArgs            " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-StartArgs"} @{"/" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-default"}   | |
        |  | ARexxPort      : @{" ARexxPort            " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-ARexxPort"} @{"/" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-default"}   | |
        |  | PublicScreen   : @{" PublicScreen         " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-PublicScreen"} @{"/" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-default"}   | |
        |  | REXX Open-File : @{" Open-File            " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-OpenFile"} @{"/" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-default"}   | |
        |  | REXX NewWindow : @{" NewWindow            " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-NewWindow"} @{"/" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-default"}   | |
        |  | Show HTML      : @{" @| Show HTML         " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Show HTML"}      | |
        |  |                                              | |
        |  +@{b}----------------------------------------------@{ub}+ |
        |               @{"Save" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Save"}   @{"Use" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Use"}   @{"Quit" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Quit"}                 |
        +@{b}---------------------------------------------------@{ub}+

 @{u}HTTP-Mails:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Main_2.iff/MAIN"}

        @{"The menu of HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Menue"}
        +@{b}---------------------------------------------------@{ub}+
        |                             @{b}____________________@{ub}  |
        |                            |     HTTP-Mail      | |
        |  +@{b}-------------------------@{ub}+                    | |
        |  | LoadWebImage   : @{" @| LoadWebImage      " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-LoadWebImage"}      | |
        |  | Make Imagelist : @{" @| Make Imagelist    " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Makeimagelist"}      | |
        |  | SaveWebImage   : @{" @| SaveWebImage      " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-SaveWebImage"}      | |
        |  | Quiet          : @{" @| Quiet             " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Quiet"}      | |
        |  | Cachepath      : @{" Cachepath            " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Cachepath"} @{"#" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Cachepath"}   | |
        |  | Downloadlist   : @{" Downloadlist         " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadlist"} @{"#" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadlist"}   | |
        |  | Downloadmanager: @{" Downloadmanager      " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadmanager"} @{"#" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadmanager"}   | |
        |  | OnOffline      : @{" OnOffline            " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-OnOffline"} @{"#" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-OnOffline"}   | |
        |  +@{b}----------------------------------------------@{ub}+ |
        |               @{"Save" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Save"}   @{"Use" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Use"}   @{"Quit" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Quit"}                 |
        +@{b}---------------------------------------------------@{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-default" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Default@{uu}

 If set, HTMLread use the internal saved default settings.
 The checkmarks are disabled if you choose the viewer »other«.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Quiet" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Quiet@{uu}

 If you choose this function the downloadmanager won't always open the status
 windows. Then you'll only find the download-informations in the statusline
 of YAM. The status windows will only be opened when you'll read a message.
 They will not be opened when you just received messages and the download-
 manager has started. 
 If you choose NO the status windows will always be opened.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-OnOffline" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}OnOffline@{uu}

 You're offline and then decide to download pictures from the web
 (Lock at @{"Make Imagelist" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Makeimagelist"}) the computer must go online.
 The OnOfflinePlugin start youre TCP/IP-Stack and go online.
 You have to tell your HTMLreadOrefs this plugin and it has to be of the
 type OnOfflinePlugin.

 The @{b}Miami@{ub} Plugin controls if MiamiDx is available. If it is available
 the plugin will try to go online with it. If MiamiDx isn't available the
 casual Miami will be used.
 The MiamiPlugin should be located at the path YAM:Rexx/. Its name is
 "MiamiOnOff.rx".

 For @{b}Genesis@{ub} choose the @{" Genesisplugin " Link "How to config GenesisPlugin?"}.
 The GenesisPlugin should be located at the path YAM:Rexx/. Its name is
 "GenesisOnOff.rx".

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadlist" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Downloadlist@{uu}

 Here you'll find the options to the list where the pictures are saved while
 you are offline. You'll find those options under @{"Make Imagelist" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Makeimagelist"}.
 Take care that you don't choose a place where the datas get lost if you 
 reset. E.g., this is ENV: because it usually is located at the RAM disc. 
 A better place is ENVARC: because it's located at the hard disc.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadmanager" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Downloadmanager@{uu}

 The downloadmanager is the most important plugin of HTMLread. It has to be
 stated and it has to be of the type HTMLreadDownloadplugin. HTMLreadPrefs
 will control this and will tell you if it is not correctly installed.
 With this Downloadmanager HTMLread downloads the pictures from the web.
 Its name is "Hrdownload.rx" and it should be in the file YAM:Rexx/.

 Right now, YAM is used to download pictures. It is planned that in future
 there will be a plugin which will do this with HTMLresume or other programs.

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"HRDownload" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HRDownload-Windows.iff/MAIN"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Cachepath" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Cachepath@{uu}

 Here you tell the computer where the pictures are saved first. The cachepath
 has to be in an own file.  You may @{b}@{u}not@{uu}@{ub} put it in MAIL: only since then datas can
 get lost!
 You can put it for example in »MAIL:HTMLread/«. This file has to exist.
 So you can make it with »makedir mail:HTMLread« for example.

 The cachepath can be controlled with @{"clearCaches" LINK "clearCache"}.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-SaveWebImage" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}SaveWebImage@{uu}

 If an email has pictures which are in the web you can download them. Here
 you can determine if the pictures are saved in a cache so you don't need
 to go online if you want to read the email with its pictures. HTMLread will
 figure out by itself if the picture is saved in the cache and then it will
 replace the picture from the web automatically. So you can also read this
 message offline with all its pictures.
 The pictures will be saved at the path which is named at the @{"Cachepath" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Cachepath"}.
 With the script @{"clearCache" LINK "clearCache"} you can control this cache.


 Ask first: Asks you if the pictures should be saved

 NO       : Doesn't save the pictures in the cache but in t: which usually
            is located in the RAM disc and will be deleted after a reset.
            (This makes sense if you have any confidential pictures.)

 YES      : Will save the pictures.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-LoadWebImage" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}LoadWebImage@{uu}

 There are emails which have pictures which are not contained in the email
 but are in the web. With LoadWebImage you can decide if HTMLread will load 
 those images from the web. You can decide this at @{"Make Imagelist" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Makeimagelist"}.

 If you already loaded those pictures and they are saved in the @{"cache" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Cachepath"}
 HTMLread will automatically insert them into the email.
 (Also if you put LoadWebImage at NO)

 YES = Load the pictures from the web.

 NO  = Leave out those pictures.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Makeimagelist" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Make Imagelist@{uu}

 If HTMLread discovers an HTML-email which contains pictures which are in the
 web and you're offline HTMLread can react differently:


 Ask first: - You are asked if you want to go online
            - Do you want to scip those pictures
            - Add to @{"Downloadlist" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadlist"}

            @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"Ask-Requester" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HRead-Online.iff/MAIN"}

 YES      : The pictures will be saved in the list automatically, you will not be asked

 NO       : The pictures will always be left out when you are offline, the
            pictures will only be loaded when you're online

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Viewer" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Viewer:@{uu}

 Here you can choose a viewer from the list. If your viewer isn`t shown,
 choose @{"»other«" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-ViewerName"}. After you have selected the viewer, a filerequester will
 show up. There you have to enter the path and the name of your HTML-viewer.

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"fileRequester" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewer-FReq.iff/MAIN"}


@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-ViewerName" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Viewername:@{uu}

 If you chose "other" then the stringinput viewername is enabled. It asks
 for the name of your own HTML-viewer.

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"viewername" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewername.iff/MAIN"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-StartArgs" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}StartARG:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"StartARG" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewername.iff/MAIN"}

 Here you can define arguments for ya viewer.(If you chose a preselected 
 one from the list, HTMLread will do this job for you.)
 
 You only have to define if: 
  
 a) you chose @{"Viewer" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Viewer"} = »other« or
 b) you don`t like the preselected args
 
 
 But, however, if you want to use different arguments, HTMLread additionally 
 gives you:
 %ys for the @{"PublicScreen" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-PublicScreen"} that you selected.
 %hm for the HTML-Mail-File.

 example:
 StartArg: "PUBSCREEN=%ys FILE=%hm"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-PublicScreen" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}PublicScreen:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"PublicScreen" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewername.iff/MAIN"}

 Define a screen for your viewer. You can submit this Screenname by the 
 variable %ys (f.ex. if you want to use a non preselected viewer with your 
 own @{"arguments" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-StartArgs"})
 
 If you type nothing, %ys automatically becomes Workbench.
 
 I recommend you to type »YAM«, this opens your viewer on the same screen 
 that YAM uses.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Path+Viewer" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Path+Viewer:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"Path+Viewer" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewer-FReq.iff/MAIN"}

 Includes Path and Programname of your chosen HTML-viewer.
 You always have to fill in if you want to use none of the preselected
 ones from the list. 

 for example:
 Path+Viewer: "SYS:Utilities/MultiView"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-ARexxPort" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}ARexxPort:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"ARexxPort" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewername.iff/MAIN"}

 If you want to control your HTML-viewer via ARexx you have to maintain the
 ARexxPortName here. (Only necessary if you chose a non-preselected viewer)
 
 If the HTML-viewer knows various ARexxPorts (f.ex. AWeb: AWEB.1, AWEB.2, 
 AWEB.3...) then HTMLread detects the right one automatically.
 For that you have to set a point ».« at portnames end.
 
 examples:

 ARexxport: "AWEB."     for various necessary ports
 ARexxport: "VOYAGER"   for a fixed port

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-OpenFile" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}REXX:OpenFile:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"REXX:OpenFile" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewername.iff/MAIN"}

 These are the ARexx-commands which were submitted when the HTML-Viewer starts. 
 Various commands have to be separated by a semicolon ";". Apart from this, 
 HTMLread  also knows the same variables like descriped under @{"StartArgs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-StartArgs"}.
 Leave this field empty if you are going to use a preselected HTML-@{"viewer" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Viewer"} from 
 the list, HTMLread knows the right ARexx commands.

 example:
 REXX:OpenFile: "OPENURL FILE://localhost/%hm;SCREENTOFRONT"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-NewWindow" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}REXX:NewWindow:@{uu}

 @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"REXX:NewWindow" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HPrefs-Viewername.iff/MAIN"}

 These are the ARexx-commands which were submitted while the HTML-Viewer is running.
 Various commands have to be separated by a semicolon ";". Apart from this, 
 HTMLread  also knows the same variables like descriped under @{"StartArgs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-StartArgs"}.
 Leave this field empty if you are going to use a preselected HTML-@{"viewer" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Viewer"} from 
 the list, HTMLread knows the right ARexx commands.


 example:
 REXX:NewWindow: "OPENURL NEWWIN file://localhost/%hm;SHOW;SCREENTOFRONT"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Show HTML" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Show HTML-Mail:@{uu}

 Here you can choose how HTMLread should behave if it detects a HTMLmail:

 ALL                     = Show all HTML-documents without asking!
                           Show Attachments as well!
 Ask befor               = same but asks. @{b}picture@{ub}: @{"Ask-Message" LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/HRead-Ask.iff/MAIN"}
 Only first mailpart     = Only checks the 1st document in a mail,
                           starts the viewer if need be.
                           Only Shows HTMLmails without additional
                           ascii-text.
 Only 1st & 2nd mailpart = Only checks the 1st and the 2nd  document 
                           in a mail, starts the viewer if need be.
                           If a mail consists of ascii-text
                           and HTMLcode, both of them are showed.
@ENDNODE


@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Save" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Save:@{uu}

 Save the config.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Use" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Use:@{uu}

 Do only save to ENV: not to ENVARC: .

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Quit" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Quit:@{uu}

 quits HTMLreadPrefs!

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HTMLreadPrefs-Menue" "How to use HTMLreadPrefs?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}The menu of HTMLreadPrefs:@{uu}

        +@{b}------------@{ub}+@{b}--@{ub}+@{b}---------------@{ub}+@{b}-----@{ub}...
        | Project    |  | HTMLreadPrefs |
        |@{b}------------@{ub}+@{b}--@{ub}+@{b}---------------@{ub}+@{b}-----@{ub}...
        | About      |  | Font          |
        |@{b}------------@{ub}|  | Snapshot      |
        | Open       |  | @{b}MicroRexx@{ub}     |
        | Last Saved |  |@{b}---------------@{ub}|
        | Save As    |  | Load          |
        |@{b}------------@{ub}|  | Save          |
        | Quit       |  +@{b}---------------@{ub}+
        +@{b}------------@{ub}+

 @{u}Project:@{uu}

 About      : shows the version of the program
 Open       : loads the HRDownload.liste under another name
 Last Saved : loads the last HRDownload.liste
 Save As    : saves the HRDownload.liste under another name
 Quit       : quits DownloadPrefs

 @{u}HTMLreadPrefs:@{uu}

 Font     : here you can choose the font:
            SystemFont: You use youre normal font (Prefs/Font).
 Snapshot : The windowposition for the window.
 @{b}MicroRexx@{ub}: If no MicroRexx is running HTMLreadPrefs must start MicroRexx.
            Set here the path and MicroRexx.
 Load     : loads the HTMLreadPrefsonfig.
 Save     : saves the HTMLreadPrefsonfig to ENV(ARC):HTMLreadPrefs/

@ENDNODE

@NODE "work HTMLread" "How HTMLread works?"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}How HTMLread works@{uu}

 After correct Installation of HTMLread, everytime you read a Mail, YAM
 executes HTMLread.rx. It checks if the mail includes HTMLcode (MIME-Type 
 TEXT/HTML, this is the identifer for a HTMLdocument). If yes, HTMLread also
 checks the existence of pictures, saves them and changes the
 picturepath in the HTML source in a way, that your preferred HTML
 interpreter can find and show them. If this is done, HTMLread starts your
 HTMLviewer.
 Of course HTMLread can handle several HTMLdocuments in one email.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Optimizer" "Optimizer!"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Der Optimizer@{uu}

 (removed)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Fehlermeldungen" "Errormessages:"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{u}Errormessages@{uu}

 @{b}@{u}HTMLread seems not to work!@{ub}@{uu}
 @{"Help! HTMLread doesn`t work!" LINK "Help!"}
 Take a look at @{"How to install" LINK "How to install"} chapter f).

 @{b}@{u}No HTMLread-configfile!@{ub}@{uu}
 The chosen configfile is not from type HTMLreadConfig. the first line in
 the configfile has to be:
 # HTMLread.config  !!Do not edit the first line!!

 @{b}@{u}Problem to open the configfile!@{ub}@{uu}
 The configfile simply donesn`t exist.  There are two possibilities:
 a) Save a new one by using @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs"} with the same
    path and name.
 b) You set a wrong configfile in YAM/Konfig/ARexx/
    »When reading a message«. Please correct or delete it. (If none is set,
    HTMLread automatically takes ENV:HTMLread.config)

 @{b}@{u}Unknown keyword found in configfile!@{ub}@{uu}
 HTMLread found an unknown keyword in the configfile. HTMLread only accepts
 the following keywords:
 @{" viewer " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Viewer"}, @{" path " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Path+Viewer"}, @{" startarg " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-StartArgs"}, @{" pubscreen " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-PublicScreen"}, @{" arexxport " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-ARexxPort"},
 @{" arexxopenfile " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-OpenFile"}, @{" arexxnewwindow " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-OpenFile"}, @{" showhtml " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Show HTML"}, @{" loadwebimage " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-LoadWebImage"},
 @{" downloadmanager" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadmanager"}, @{" savewebimage " LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-SaveWebImage"}, @{"downloadlist" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Downloadlist"}, @{"makeimagelist" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Makeimagelist"},
 @{"onoffline" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-OnOffline"}, @{"webimagepath" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Cachepath"}, @{"quiet" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-quiet"}.
 Take care that the arguments of this keyword are include in "".
 Correct or delete the line or save a new configfile with HTMLreadPrefs.

 @{b}@{u}The »@{"Viewer" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Viewer"}« or »@{"path" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Path+Viewer"}« is not correct!@{ub}@{uu}
 One of these keywords is not set correctly (empty). Please load and save the
 configfile with HTMLreadPrefs.

 @{b}@{u}I need this keyword unconditional!@{ub}@{uu}
 The shown keyword must be included in the configfile to run HTMLread 
 correctly. Please load and save the configfile with @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs"}.

 @{b}@{u}Warning, Keyword not found!@{ub}@{uu}
 The shown keyword is not included in the configfile. HTMLread takes 
 the default and starts. Please load and save the configfile with @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs"}.

 @{b}@{u}Program does not exists!@{ub}@{uu}
 HTMLread wants to start your HTMLviewer but the program doesn't exist.
 Please start @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs"} and choose the 
 CORRECT @{"path+viewer" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-Path+Viewer"}
 .

 @{b}@{u}I can not find the @{"ARexxPort" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-ARexxPort"}!@{ub}@{uu}
 The given ARexxport doesn't exist. Start @{"HTMLreadPrefs" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs"} and check
 the arexxport and the belonging HTMLviewer.

 @{b}@{u}The ARexx-comand-returncode is not 0 !@{ub}@{uu}
 HTMLread sends an arexxcomand to your HTMLviewer but the HTMLviewer sends back
 an errorreturncode. Check if the ARexxcommand is correct. Maybe the HTMLviewer
 only is a demo or a SE-version? Many of them can`t handle all rexxcommands.
 @{"arexxopenfile" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-OpenFile"} @{"arexxnewwindow" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-REXX-OpenFile"}

@ENDNODE

