@NODE "How to config GenesisPlugin?" "How to config GenesisPlugin"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{U}How to config GenesisPlugin@{UU}

 a) run youre editor.
    ( or use this button if you have
      - OS 2.0 - 3.1 @{" C:ED YAM:Rexx/GENESISonoff.rx " SYSTEM "RUN C:ED YAM:Rexx/GENESISonoff.rx"}
      - OS 3.5 - 3.9 @{" SYS:Tools/EditPad YAM:Rexx/GENESISonoff.rx " SYSTEM "RUN SYS:Tools/EditPad YAM:Rexx/GENESISonoff.rx"} )

 b) in line 4 you find follow text:
    interface  = "Youre Interface"    /* Please enter between the " youre Interface */

    Please enter here youre interface. The interface is shown in the the
    GENESiS-Window under Interface:
    @{b}Picture@{ub}: @{" The Genesis Window " LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/Genesis-Win.iff/MAIN"} (OS 3.9)
    In my case is the line 4:
    interface  = "Callino"    /* Please enter between the " youre Interface */

    (Note: Do not change the first line !!)

 c) Save now.
    (If you use ED (OS 2.0 - 3.1) press ESC than x and than ENTER)

 d) Please start HTMLreadPrefs.
    ( You find HTMLreadPrefs.rx in YAM:HTMLread/ )

 e) Go to HTTP-Mails.

 f) Change @{"OnOffline" LINK "HTMLreadPrefs-OnOffline"} to GENESISonoff.rx .
    @{b}Picture@{ub}: @{" The Genesis Window " LINK "HTMLdok-Picture/Genesis-HPrefs.iff/MAIN"}

 g) Save youre prefs

Ready

@ENDNODE

@NODE "EMail is watching you!" "EMail is watching you!"

 @{u}@{b}Espionage by means of HTML-Emails@{ub}@{uu}

 HTMLmails are not just looking better than ordinary ones, they also 
 have the "advantage" of giving the sender the possibility to watch the 
 behaviour of the recipient (means YOU) in some cases. 
 The trick is far easy: a link to an invisible 1x1 pixel picture which is 
 reserved for your mail, becomes built into the HTML source and as soon as 
 your Htmlviewer starts loading it down, the sender knows that you opened 
 his mail. Its also possible to transmit a JavaScript that, when executed, 
 conveys  datas to the sender.
 
 For doing this there are special Internetservices, one of them for example
 is http://www.itraceyou.com. 

 The only way to avoid this kind of snooping is not to load down pictures 
 from these internetservices and to disable the JavaScript interpretation of 
 the browser.
 Therefore HTMLread gives you the option not to load down pictures from 
 defined Internet adresses.
 The only restriction is that HTMLread has to know the adresses of Internet-
 services which want to send these bad agents to your computer. For that, 
 HTMLread uses a database in which are stored all the well-known  of these 
 adresses. The database is called »badurls.htmlread« and  can be found in your
 YAM: drawer. It`s a common textfile where you can enter additional url`s
 with an ascii editor (ed, edidpad etc.)
 You just have to type the URL without http://www
 
 example:
 For http://www.itraceyou.com the entry is: itraceyou.com
 
 From now on HTMLread won`t load pictures from these adresses anymore and the
 bad "agent" can`t find out that you read the mail.


 IF you know some more of these URL`s I would like to please @{b}all@{ub} of you to 
 inform @{"me" LINK "Who wrote this"} as soon as possible. Then I will release an updated @{i}BadUrl-list@{ui}
 on my HomePage @{i}http://www.htmlread.50g.com@{ui} 


@ENDNODE
